						<summary><p>#142. a) Tiruvaiyāṟu, Tiruvaiyāṟu taluk, Tanjavur district, Pañcanātīśvara temple; b) on the easternmost pilaster of the southern façade of the <foreign>mukha-maṇḍapa</foreign>; c) I have located the inscription in situ, but could not read it because it is very damaged; d) ARE 1894, no. 252; SII 5, no. 551; e) 14th regnal year of Kōpparakesarivarman; f) probably Parāntaka I (<foreign>circa</foreign> 921 A.D.); g) inscription not read with anyone; h) I rely mostly on the edition established in SII, because the inscription is today almost illegible.</p>

