<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 14th year of Kōpparakesarivarman. To Mahādeva of Tiruvaiyāṟu, for a perpetual lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nantāviḷakku</foreign> &gt; <foreign>nontāviḷakku</foreign></supplied> to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>erivataṟku</foreign></supplied> night and day, Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyaṉ Kaṇṭaṉ Amutaṉ, for one <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oṉṟiṉukku</foreign></supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">lamp</supplied>, as long as the sun and the moon endure, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭutta</foreign></supplied> ninety <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>toṇṇūṟu</foreign></supplied> goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭu</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Paṉmāheśvaras.</p></div>

